choices.text:
Facebook and stuff. “They want to talk to online friends instead of meeting them in real life…” according to my neighbour. I wish some of that obsession would shift to other things. I mean… kids in Cambodia have much stress in their daily lives… I wish they could have some kind of relief!

(hanging out with teenagers who smoke is still okay but hanging out with couples… Billie sings. It’s so awkward to hear them speak in Khmer. Imagine: “Naa Tum Sarah Wassang”. Yes it’s Sarah Wassung… but their client here is the LOVE BETWEEN SAM AND SARAH! And their wish that those two would have a permanent relationship strengthens my heart!

“Noo Sarah. Itsoh gooo”. “……..”

I feel a little sorry for you. But I will never wish them Rae romance too coz of the love relationship between Sam and I. And don’t challenge Sam at all isn’t he a stupid? Your high point is eliminated at once when you create any comment about him. I don’t challenge you, but I’m a little wonder how could you challenge him endlessly by creating comment about him via internet. I’me neither a NGO nor involve in any particular job but I don’t need charity and i can not read meaningless word for long time coz of people like you. Here no people read your blog like this; nobody in Cambodia and nobody in other. I’m your only visitor here and it is a little ashamed but I
